-- Google Share of U.S. Smartphone Market Tops 50%, ComScore Says
-- B y   L i s a   R a p a p o r t
-- 2012-05-01T15:55:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-01/google-share-of-u-s-smartphone-market-tops-50-comscore-says.html
Google Inc. (GOOG) ’s Android operating system
powered 51 percent of U.S. smartphones in the three months ended
March 31,  ComScore Inc. (SCOR)  said today.  Apple Inc. (AAPL)  ranked second, with 31 percent, followed by
 Research In Motion Ltd. (RIM) , with 12 percent. Google’s share in the
previous three-month period was 47 percent, ComScore said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
